calculate msft & aapl daily in logarithmatic and also arithmetic term

msft_prc <- msft %>% select(date,prc) %>%
  arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(lag.prc=lag(prc,1)) %>%
  mutate(msft.ret.l=log(prc/lag.prc)) %>%
  mutate(msft.ret.a=prc/lag.prc-1) %>%
  select(date,msft.ret.l,msft.ret.a)

aapl_prc <- aapl %>% select(date,prc) %>% 
  arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(lag.prc=lag(prc,1))  %>%
  mutate(aapl.ret.l=log(prc/lag.prc)) %>%
  mutate(aapl.ret.a=prc/lag.prc-1) %>%
  select(date,aapl.ret.l,aapl.ret.a)

merge msft and aapl returns based on date

msft_aapl = merge(aapl_prc, msft_prc, by = 'date')
print(head(msft_aapl))

calculate long-short returns in logarithmatic and arithmetic term

msft_aapl = msft_aapl %>% mutate(msft.aapl.ret.l = msft.ret.l -aapl.ret.l)%>%
  mutate(msft.aapl.ret.a = msft.ret.a - aapl.ret.a)

calculate long-short cumulative returns

msft_aapl = msft_aapl %>% arrange(date) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(msft.aapl.ret.l)) %>%
  mutate(cumret.l=cumprod(msft.aapl.ret.l +1))

cat('the total logarithmatic cumulative return is', tail(msft_aapl$cumret.l,1))
## the total logarithmatic cumulative return is 1.367634

compare with the arithmetic cumulative return

msft_aapl = msft_aapl %>% arrange(date) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(msft.aapl.ret.a)) %>%
  mutate(cumret.a=cumprod(msft.aapl.ret.a +1))

cat('the total arithmetic cumulative return is', tail(msft_aapl$cumret.a,1))
## the total arithmetic cumulative return is 1.36181

Question 2.b plot two lines on the same chart

calculate cumulative return for aapl and msft

msft_prc = msft_prc %>% arrange(date) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(msft.ret.l)) %>%
  mutate(msft.cum = cumprod(msft.ret.l +1))

aapl_prc = aapl_prc %>% arrange(date) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(aapl.ret.l)) %>%
  mutate(aapl.cum = cumprod(aapl.ret.l +1))

making plot of the cumulative returns for the two stocks

yrange= range(msft_prc$msft.cum, aapl_prc$aapl.cum)
plot(msft_prc$msft.cum ~ as.Date(msft_prc$date), type='l',
     ylab='cumulative returns', xlab='date',
     ylim = yrange,
     main='cumulative returns of MSFT and AAPL',col='red')
lines(aapl_prc$aapl.cum ~ as.Date(aapl_prc$date), col='blue')
legend('topleft',c('MSFT cumulative returns','AAPL cumulative returns'),
       lty=c(1,1),col=c('red','blue'))

Question 2.c cumulative returns for new strategy

mutate a signal column

msft_aapl= msft_aapl %>% mutate (msft.aapl.lag = lag(msft.aapl.ret.a, 1)) %>%
  mutate (mysignal = ifelse(msft.aapl.lag >=0, 1, -1))%>%
  mutate (newret = mysignal*msft.aapl.ret.a)
print(head(msft_aapl$newret))
## [1]           NA -0.014665087  0.001316866  0.009004128  0.009477666
## [6] -0.012138023

calculate cumulative returns of the new strategy

msft_aapl = msft_aapl %>% arrange(date) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(newret)) %>%
  mutate(cumret.new = cumprod(newret +1))

show the cumulative returns

yrange = range(msft_aapl[,c('cumret.a', 'cumret.new')])
plot(msft_aapl$cumret.a ~ as.Date(msft_aapl$date), type='l',
     ylab='cumulative returns', xlab='date', 
     ylim= yrange,
     main='cumulative returns of long-short strategy and the new strategy',col='blue')
lines(msft_aapl$cumret.new ~ as.Date(msft_aapl$date), col='red')
legend('topleft',c('long-short strategy','new strategy'),
       lwd=1,col=c('blue','red'))

cat('the total return of the new strategy is', tail(msft_aapl$cumret.new, 1))
## the total return of the new strategy is 1.252082

Question 3 user defined function of Bollinger Bands

obtain closing prices of aapl and msft

library(zoo)
## 
## Attaching package: 'zoo'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     as.Date, as.Date.numeric
setwd('/Users/dongliyuan/Desktop/FIN3380/L1')
msft = read.csv("msft.csv")
msft = msft %>% select(date, prc, permno) %>%
  arrange(date)

define a function to get bollinger bands

Mybb = function(x, window) {
  avg = rollmean(x, k=window, fill=NA, align ='right')
  sd = rollapply(x, width= window, FUN=sd, na.rm=T, fill=NA, align='right')
  sd2up = avg + 2*sd
  sd2down = avg - 2*sd
  rst = data.frame(prc = x, avg = avg, sd2up=sd2up, sd2down=sd2down)
  return(rst)
}

call the function

bbtest = Mybb(msft$prc, 15)
print(bbtest[12:18,])
##      prc      avg    sd2up  sd2down

make plot

bbtest = bbtest %>% mutate (date = msft$date)

     xlab='date',

     type='l',
     main='MSFT: Bollinger Bands')
